RIYADH: Digital version of books are reshaping the educational sector, said Apple co-founder Steve Wozniak, while talking at GEC 2022 in Riyadh on Sunday. “I used to think that computers would change education. But eventually, I found out that it was (the) digital version of books,” said Wozniak.   Talking about the emerging interest in space, Wozniak noted that the advent of Elon Musk’s Starlink is helping people to access the Internet without depending on infrastructure on the ground. He added that the emergence of satellite phones has made communication very easy, and now, even a ship out in the ocean could easily communicate with the ground. Wozniak revealed that he never wanted to start a company, instead, he wished to be an engineer.